  "educationalNotes": "Indium is rare silvery metal - tick-tock sound when bent (tin cry)! Indium tin oxide (ITO) is transparent electrode in touchscreens and solar cells - critical for all modern displays. Indium arsenide semiconductors used in infrared detectors. Very soft metal - indium foil easily dented. Discovered in 1863. Named after indigo color of spectral line. Supply comes mainly from zinc mining byproduct. High price due to rarity."
